Angelo CALABRESE, an Incompetent, by Lucia Calabrese, his Wife, Appellant, v. Jerome G. LOCKE, Deputy Commissioner, United States Employees’ Compensation Commission, Second Compensation Department, Appellee. No. 327. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 5, 1934. Robert I. Rogin, of New York City, for appellant. George Z. Medalie, of New York City, for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (56 F.(2d) 458) affirmed.
